
Login to Get a Token:

Make a POST request to /api/v1/auth/login with your email and password.
Copy the token from the response:
json
Copy code
{
  "message": "Login successful",
  "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..."
}
Add the Token to the Header:

When accessing the /protected route, include this header:
makefile
Copy code
Authorization: Bearer <your-token>
Example using Postman:

Go to the Headers tab.
Add a key-value pair:
makefile
Copy code
Key: Authorization
Value: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
Access the Protected Route:

Make a GET request to /protected.
If the token is valid, you'll see:
csharp
Copy code
Hello, your role is: viewer
If the token is invalid or missing, you'll get a 401 Unauthorized response:
json
Copy code
{
  "message": "Unauthorized: Invalid token"
}
##################################################################################################################

Test the following endpoints:
Create a User (Admin only):

POST /api/v1/users/add-user
Request body:
json
Copy code
{
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "editor"
}
Get All Users (Admin only):

GET /api/v1/users
Update User (Admin only):

PUT /api/v1/users/update-user/:userId
Request body:
json
Copy code
{
  "email": "updateduser@example.com",
  "role": "viewer"
}
Delete User (Admin only):

DELETE /api/v1/users/delete-user/:userId


